16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Spoon batter into baking cups, filling about 2/3 full.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Bake 22 to 24 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Cool in pans for 5 minutes and then remove from pans and cool completely before frosting.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 For icing, beat shortening, butter and lime zest with mixer until smooth.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Gradually add sugar 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Add tequila and beat until light and fluffy.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Spread icing onto cupcakes. Sprinkle green sanding sugar around the edge of the cupcakes and garnish with additional lime zest.
16022aa1-e556-4249-aed7-3e1ded58ea63 Cut a small opening at the tip of the Shot Tops Infuser. Place the cut opening into the tequila and squeeze the top to fill. Insert the cut end into the cupcakes. When ready to eat, squeeze the top of Shot Tops Infuser again to infuse cake with tequila.
ff880457-c1eb-41fc-b62f-830b44633b33 Gather the ingredients.
ff880457-c1eb-41fc-b62f-830b44633b33 In a small dish or bowl, combine the soymilk and vinegar and allow to rest for 3-5 minutes or until thickened slightly. Mix in cornstarch or arrowroot, stirring to dissolve. Set aside.
ff880457-c1eb-41fc-b62f-830b44633b33 In a blender or food processor, process the cashews until finely ground. Set aside.
ff880457-c1eb-41fc-b62f-830b44633b33 In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine water, lemon juice, nutritional yeast, spices, and tahini. Stir in ground cashews and soymilk mixture until well blended. Stir in prepared salsa and salt. Cook until desired consistency, keeping in mind that mixture will thicken slightly as it cools. Salt to taste.
ff880457-c1eb-41fc-b62f-830b44633b33 Serve warm, at room temperature or cold with tortilla or pita chips, or use as a sauce for tacos, quesadillas or burritos.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Gather the ingredients.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Select the sauté button on the Instant Pot and add about half of the oil to the inner pot. When the oil is hot and shimmering, add about half of the beef. Cook until well browned on all sides. Remove the beef to a plate. Repeat with the remaining oil and beef. Remove the beef to the plate.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b In a bowl, combine the stock, vinegar, lime juice, peppers, adobo sauce, cumin, oregano, salt, pepper, and cloves; stir until blended. Add the liquids and seasonings to the pot and stir, scraping up any browned bits in the bottom of the pot.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Add the beef back to the Instant Pot along with the bay leaves.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Place the lid on the Instant Pot and lock it in place. Turn the valve to the sealing position and select pressure cook or manual setting (high pressure). Set the time for 45 minutes.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b When the time is up, let the pressure come down naturally for about 10 minutes. Carefully turn the valve to the venting position to release the remaining pressure.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Remove the beef to a pan or bowl and shred it with two forks. Add the liquids to the beef. If you aren't serving immediately, add the shredded beef back to the pot and keep it on the warm setting.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Serve the beef in soft or crisp corn tortillas with fresh salsa, lime wedges, and chopped cilantro.
0d1bfa8c-8fba-4ca7-a566-8ac2e19fb50b Enjoy!
c15e9b88-35b7-438e-b35e-f10caea4b40b Gather the ingredients.
c15e9b88-35b7-438e-b35e-f10caea4b40b Mix tomatoes, onions, chilies, garlic, cilantro, and oil until all items are coated in the oil.
c15e9b88-35b7-438e-b35e-f10caea4b40b Mix in lime, water, and tequila.
c15e9b88-35b7-438e-b35e-f10caea4b40b Leave as is for a chunky style of salsa or puree in a blender or food processor for a smooth, paste style.
c15e9b88-35b7-438e-b35e-f10caea4b40b Add salt and pepper to taste.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Gather your ingredients.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Preheat the oven to 375F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper and set aside. Brush both sides of each tortilla with the melted butter. Stack them after they have been brushed.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Dust each buttered tortilla with cinnamon sugar on both sides.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Cut each tortilla into 6 wedges. You can cut them individually or stack them and cut them to save time.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Place the wedges on the prepared baking sheets. Do not let them overlap. Sprinkle the tops with extra cinnamon sugar.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Bake them in the preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp and the sugar has slightly caramelized. Allow them to cool before topping them!
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Gather the ingredients for the cream cheese icing.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Whisk together the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar, vanilla extract, and milk in a small bowl. Place it in a decorating bag or a zip-top bag with the tip cut off.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Melt the chocolate chips in the microwave in 30-second increments, stirring in between until completely smooth.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Chop the strawberries in a small dice. Then toss them with the tablespoon of granulated sugar.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Arrange the tortillas on your serving plate.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Drizzle the cinnamon sugar chips with the melted chocolate and cream cheese icing. Then top with the chopped strawberries.
fd2e6b8b-60d5-49d3-878a-59e002478f11 Top with a few squirts of whipped cream and serve immediately!
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Gather your ingredients.
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Fill a chilled beer mug or pint glass halfway with ice.
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Add the lime juice, sauces, and pepper.
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Stir until well mixed.
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Slowly top with beer and garnish with a slice of lime.
c487d7a9-a628-4944-883f-9fd9971e30ae Serve and enjoy!
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c Gather the ingredients.
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c Add a three-colored sugar rim to a small tumbler or margarita glass: Begin by wetting a third of the rim with a lime wedge, then roll it in green sugar. Wet an adjoining third of the glass with the lime and roll it in white sugar. Repeat with the last third of the rim, this time rolling it in red sugar.
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c In a mixing glass or cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the tequila, fruit juices and soda.
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c Stir well then squeeze in the juice from a lime wedge and stir again.
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c Strain the drink into the rimmed glass.
47cd0afb-d745-4ed4-b400-30a9d5d2805c Serve and enjoy!
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Preheat the oven to 400 F.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Slice each corn tortilla into 8 triangles. To slice the tortillas with a pizza cutter, simply lay the corn tortillas flat.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Then cut each in half.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Then cut the tortilla in half again 90 degrees the other way.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Then cut each fourth in half and you and up with eight uniform triangles.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Next, place the tortilla triangles in a single layer on a large baking sheet that has been coated with a light layer of cooking spray.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c For extra flavor and crispiness, next, spray each triangle with just a bit of cooking spray, and sprinkle the salt evenly over all of the "chips".
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Place the tortilla chips in the oven, and bake them for 10 minutes, or until they begin to become crisp and they are lightly browned only near the edges.
2efec25a-56d9-41fb-b0f5-24265f32b24c Be sure not to overcook the chips or they may become burnt and will not taste very good.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Gather the ingredients.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Cut the crusts off of the slices of white bread. Using a rolling pin, flatten each slice of bread until they're completely flat.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Whisk together the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar, and vanilla extract.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Spread some of the cream cheese mixture onto each of the slices of the white bread. Place four blueberries across the short end of the bread.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Roll the slice of bread over the blueberries and continue until it's completely rolled and then seal the end by pressing the edge lightly against the cylinder.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Whisk together the eggs, sugar, vanilla extract, and whole milk in a medium-sized bowl until completely combined.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Dip each one of the rollups into the egg wash. Dip twice to allow for extra absorption.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Heat a griddle on medium-high heat. Add butter to the griddle.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Place the roll-ups on the griddle and cook until golden brown. Rotate the roll-ups until every side has been cooked and is golden brown.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Top additional blueberries, powdered sugar, and maple syrup.
8ec40288-80e6-4117-acf2-4094d71cc5d3 Serve and enjoy!
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Heat a heavy 10-inch skillet over medium heat. Dice the bacon, and add it to the hot skillet. Cook the bacon until it is crisp, turning to brown both sides. Remove the bacon to paper towels to drain. Set aside.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Shred the cheese using a food processor with the shredding disk or use a box grater. Set aside.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Position an oven rack in the lower third of the oven.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Heat oven to 425 F.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 In a large bowl or in an electric blender, combine the eggs, flour, milk, Dijon mustard, kosher salt, and pepper. Whisk or process until the batter is smooth.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Wipe the heavy 10-inch skillet out, and add 3 tablespoons of butter. Place the skillet over medium heat, and swirl the butter so that it coats the bottom and sides. When the foaming subsides, pour the batter into the skillet.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Combine the shredded cheese and cooked bacon, and sprinkle over the center of the egg batter, leaving an edge of about 1 inch to allow the batter to puff as it bakes.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Bake for about 15 to 17 minutes, or until the pancake is browned and puffed around the edge. Turn the oven temperature down to 325 F, and let it cook for about 3 to 5 minutes longer, or until set.
ddfee27b-f779-4d2f-864c-c9309ef8dbf7 Remove the pancake from the oven, and garnish with chives or parsley. Slice into wedges, and serve hot.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Gather your ingredients.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Wipe the strawberries with paper towels and remove the green stem with a kitchen knife. Slice the strawberries into quarters.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Place the sliced strawberries in a mixing bowl and add the pepper, sugar, and lemon zest. Stir gently, cover with a clean dish towel, and leave for 1 hour in the refrigerator.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Remove the strawberries from the fridge and transfer to a food processor, or you can use a stick blender, and blitz until smooth and foamy. Set aside, cover again with a dish towel, and leave to settle while you make the cream.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Whisk the mascarpone cheese with the vanilla and powdered sugar until light and airy. Pop the bowl into the fridge to chill slightly, along with four bowls, for 5 minutes.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 To Serve: Carefully ladle the strawberry soup into the chilled bowls — any large bubbles will dissipate with a gentle tap on the side of the bowl. Use a dessert spoon to scoop up a ball of the mascarpone mixture, or if you want a more professional presentation, using two dessert spoons, you can roll the mascarpone into a quenelle.
d4f4ea90-2cea-4592-b1cc-351654371c05 Dot the soup with the balsamic glaze, decorate with small leaves of basil, and serve immediately.
f8de2649-7fd7-4367-a898-1d2293b03982 Start by greasing and lining the sides and base of a 20cm / 8" diameter springform cake tin with greaseproof paper.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Preheat the oven to 400F/200C Gas 6
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Start by chilling a large mixing bowl in the freezer for 10 minutes or 30 in the fridge.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Sieve the flour and baking powder together into the large mixing bowl. Add the butter and rub into the flour working as quickly until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs, do this as fast as possible, so the mixture does not become warm.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Add the caster sugar and the lavender, stir with a metal spoon.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Reserve 2 tablespoons of egg (for glazing) then add to the mixture with 3/4 of the milk. Using a dinner knife (not your hands) mix to create a soft, dough―if the dough feels dry add a little more milk but take care not to make the dough too sticky.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Tip the dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently and lightly to help smoothen taking care not to be too heavy or knead too long.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Roll―again carefully―into a circle at least 2 cm deep.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Dip a 6 cm cutter into your bag of flour and cut out the scones avoiding twisting the cutter (this can prevent the scones from rising). Reform the dough trimmings into a ball and repeat as above until you have used it all up.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Place close together but not touching on a lightly greased baking sheet and brush the tops with the beaten egg. Bake in the center of the preheated oven for approximately 10 to 12 minutes or until golden and risen. Check the base of the scones to make sure it also is golden.
0d93b1e5-dc9c-4311-a3a1-b8d246154b3c Place on a cooling rack.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Gather your ingredients.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Place the graham crackers and sugar in a food processor and process until completely crumbled. Drizzle in the melted butter.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Press the graham cracker crust into 6 greased mini cheesecake molds. If you are using a muffin tin, make sure to use liners. Bake for 5 to 10 minutes at 350 F or until lightly browned.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Beat the softened cream cheese with the sugar and vanilla extract until combined and fluffy.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Fold the whipped cream topping into the cream cheese mixture.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Fill the prepared molds with the cream cheese filling. Fill the molds a little bit at a time. Then press down on the top of the filling with a spoon or spatula so they completely fill the mold and there are no gaps or pockets of air.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours, or until completely chilled and firm.
8093ea73-6f2a-4ea8-a885-553ec2b6a756 Remove the cheesecakes from the molds, top with fresh berries and serve! They can also be kept chilled for up to 2 days before serving!
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Gather the ingredients.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Whisk the buttermilk, eggs, 1 teaspoon of the salt, and 1 teaspoon of the pepper in a large bowl. Add the cubed steaks to the bowl and cover the bowl and refrigerate for at least one hour but up to overnight. Make sure to submerge the steaks in the buttermilk mixture.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Whisk together the flour, remaining salt, pepper, onion powder, and paprika in a shallow dish. Set aside 2 tablespoons of the seasoned flour for the gravy.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Remove 1 steak from the buttermilk mixture and dredge it in the flour mixture, coating both sides. Place the steak back into the buttermilk mixture, coating both sides. Then place the steak back into the flour mixture, coating once more. Repeat with the remaining steaks.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Place the steaks on top of a cooling rack over a sheet pan and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Add the oil to a large cast-iron skillet or other heavy-bottomed pan. Heat the oil to 350 F. Add the steaks, frying for 3 to 4 minutes per side. Remove the steaks and place them onto another clean cooling rack over a baking sheet. Keep warm in a 200 F oven.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Gather the ingredients for the gravy.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Add the butter to the remaining oil and then add the 2 tablespoons of reserved flour. Whisk until the flour is incorporated into the oil. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until the flour is lightly browned.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Pour the beef broth and hot sauce into the pan while whisking. Bring the gravy to a boil and then turn the heat to low and simmer, whisking occasionally for another 3 minutes.
e0b40116-466a-4384-97e1-a56b102dbad9 Remove the steaks form the warm oven, top them with the gravy, and serve alongside your favorite sides.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Gather the ingredients.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Cut the pointy end of a strawberry off so that the berry can stand up on its own.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Hull the strawberry. Then cut a hole in the top of the berry to hold the filling, being careful not to cut all the way through to the bottom. Repeat with the remaining strawberries.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac In a medium mixing bowl, combine the cream cheese, powdered sugar, heavy cream, lemon juice, and vanilla extract. Beat with a hand mixer until well mixed and creamy.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac In a small bowl, combine the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, and sugar. Mix to combine.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Add the cheesecake filling to a piping bag and pipe it into the center of each strawberry. If you don’t have a piping bag you can fill a ziplock bag and cut off a corner and use that instead. You can also fill with a small spoon if needed.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Top with a dollop of whipped cream, if using. Sprinkle the top of each strawberry with the graham cracker crumbs. Chill, covered, in the refrigerator for 30 minutes to allow the cream cheese filling to firm up a bit, or up to 24 hours.
86569c54-094a-422c-8f57-14e1aed5d6ac Serve and enjoy!
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Gather the ingredients.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Position the oven rack to the lowest position in your oven. Preheat to 425 F. Slice the potatoes to 1/8 inch thick using a mandoline or a very sharp knife.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Place the sliced potatoes into a bowl of cold water. Stir the potatoes around and allow to sit for 10 minutes.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Remove the potatoes from the water and place in a colander to drain. Spread the potatoes onto a paper towel-lined baking sheet and pat dry. Allow to sit for another 15 minutes or so, until as dry as possible.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 While the potatoes are drying, add 2 tablespoons of the butter to a 10-inch cast-iron skillet. Heat on medium-high heat and add the sliced onion and 1 teaspoon of salt. Saute until soft and caramelized, about 12 minutes. Remove the onions from the pan and set aside.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Whisk together 7 tablespoons of the butter and the roasted garlic, cornstarch, garlic powder, remaining 1/2 teaspoon salt, and black pepper in a large bowl.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Toss the potatoes with the butter and garlic mixture until they are completely coated.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter to the same cast-iron skillet. Swirl the butter to coat the bottom of the pan completely.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Place one slice of potato in the center of you skillet, working in a circle, start adding more potato slices, slightly overlapping them until you have a full circle formed over the bottom of the pan.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Repeat with another circular layer of potatoes and then more cheese and onions. Continue until you have used all of your potatoes and cheese. Try to keep the layers as even as possible in thickness.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Heat the skillet over medium-high heat for five minutes. Coat the top of the potatoes with nonstick cooking spray and place a piece of parchment paper or aluminum foil over the top so it completely covers the surface. Add another pan on top and weigh it down with beans, weights, or even bricks.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Place the skillet on the lowest rack of the oven and bake for 25 minutes.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Remove the top pan, weights, and foil from the potatoes. Return the skillet to the oven and cook for another 15 minutes on a rack close to the top. The tops of the potatoes should be golden brown in color and then potatoes should feel tender when pricked with a fork.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Place the skillet on the stovetop one more time. Heat to medium-high heat and cook for about 2 minutes, gently shaking the pan to release the sides of the galette.
07afb294-61b5-46ff-b05f-46c846488fb3 Sprinkle more cheese on top, cut and serve with rosemary, sour cream, and more cheese.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Gather the ingredients.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Set aside the slices of bread. (They can even be left out overnight and will actually absorb more of the egg mixture if they are slightly stale.) Whisk together the eggs, whole milk, sugar, and vanilla extract in a medium-sized bowl. Pick a size that will fit the bread easily when you are ready to dip them.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Take a slice of bread and smear it with about a fourth of the Nutella. Top that slice with another piece of bread. Repeat with the remaining slices until you have four Nutella sandwiches.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Heat a griddle or large non-stick pan on medium-high heat and grease with the butter.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Dip each sandwich into the egg mixture, coating both sides of the sandwich completely. Dip again if desired.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Place the sandwiches on the griddle and turn the heat down to medium-low. Cook for about 2 minutes or until golden brown. Flip and cook for another two minutes on the other side until golden brown and all the egg has been cooked through.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Top with whipped cream, powdered sugar, and raspberries.
bba00e3e-8e41-42c6-b90e-46c9c6d2c980 Serve and enjoy!
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Gather the ingredients.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Prepare the champagne dressing first by combining extra-virgin olive oil, champagne vinegar, whole grain dijon mustard, lemon juice, honey, salt, pepper, and garlic powder in a mason jar with lid.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Secure the lid tightly and shake well until all ingredients are well-combined. Refrigerate while you prepare your salad.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 If starting with uncooked chicken breast, prepare chicken by lightly brushing 3 chicken breasts with olive oil and sprinkling with salt and pepper.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Place in a foil or parchment paper-lined pan and bake on 350 F for 25 minutes until internal temperature of chicken reaches 165 F.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Slice chicken into pieces. Rather than baking, the chicken breast may alternatively be grilled, but substituting boneless chicken breast.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Combine chicken, quartered strawberries, walnuts, red onion, and feta cheese in a large bowl. Toss liberally. Top onto bed of mixed greens.
ce886530-32db-49a0-8890-28213fba98c7 Serve alongside champagne dressing - be sure to shake or whisk dressing well before serving, as ingredients will settle.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Gather the ingredients.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 In a large bowl, stir together the flour, sugar and baking powder.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 In another bowl, combine the egg and peanut butter until well blended.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Stir in the milk and oil.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Add the wet ingredients to the dry ingredients, stirring until just blended.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Heat a skillet over medium-high heat. Pour 1/4 cup of the batter for each pancake into the skillet. Cook until bubbles form on the surface. Flip and brown on the other side.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 In a small bowl, stir together the butter and honey.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Top each stack of pancakes with a dollop of the whipped honey butter. Garnish with chopped honey roasted peanuts.
0fa44d36-5301-447c-a681-2f2e77c65776 Enjoy!
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Gather the ingredients.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a medium-sized bowl.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Whisk together the milk, melted butter, eggs, and vanilla extract in a measuring cup and then add it to the dry ingredients. Make sure the butter has cooled slightly before adding the egg so it doesn’t start to curdle.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Generously grease the bottom and sides of the Instant Pot insert with cooking spray, butter, or cooking oil. Set the Instant Pot to sauté and heat for 2 minutes.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Pour the batter into the Instant Pot and allow to cook for 3 minutes to set the bottom. This will prevent the pancake from sticking. Cover and set on the low setting for 40 minutes.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Allow any steam to release (there will be little to no build up because of the low setting), open the Instant Pot, then check to make sure the center of the pancake comes out clean when you stick it with a toothpick.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Press the sauté button and cook for another two minutes. Do not cook for any longer or the bottom of the pancake will burn.
30703883-054b-427d-8582-b34b2a587814 Place a large plate over the top of the Instant Pot insert and carefully flip the pancake over onto the plate. Slice and serve with immediately hot maple syrup and butter.
32b16ccd-b829-4f9a-813f-9ca17abf62ed Gather the ingredients.
32b16ccd-b829-4f9a-813f-9ca17abf62ed In a cocktail shaker filled with ice cubes, pour the gin (or Cognac), simple syrup, and lemon juice.
32b16ccd-b829-4f9a-813f-9ca17abf62ed Shake well.
32b16ccd-b829-4f9a-813f-9ca17abf62ed Strain into a chilled Champagne flute that is at least half full of ice.
32b16ccd-b829-4f9a-813f-9ca17abf62ed Slowly fill with Champagne.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b Gather the ingredients.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b Use a sharp knife to slice off the woody ends of the asparagus and any tough parts on the broccolini stems. Place the trimmed veggies into a large bowl. Drizzle with the extra virgin olive oil and a light sprinkle of salt.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b Heat a griddle pan on the stove over medium heat. Add the asparagus and the broccolini and grill for 6 minutes, turning the vegetables frequently, to make sure they don't scorch. Once they are cooked through, but still firm, remove from the pan and leave to drain and cool on paper towels.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b Meanwhile, make the dressing. Cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop out the flesh into a food processor or blender. Add the sour cream, lime juice, cilantro, and a tiny pinch of salt. Blitz to create a silky dressing. If it feels thick or stiff, add a little water to loosen it.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b Cook your fresh or frozen peas by either steaming or dropping into lightly boiling water for a few minutes, taking care not to overcook—they should remain firm and bright green.
f88758e1-58d6-4c5b-bbfb-dfd46364ef8b To assemble the salad, pile the asparagus and broccolini into the center of the plate. Sprinkle with the peas and the crumbled feta. Drizzle the dressing on or around the salad or serve on the side.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Gather the ingredients.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Build the tomato juice and lemon juice into a highball glass over ice cubes.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Mix well.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Add the Worcester sauce, salt, pepper, and hot sauce to taste.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Garnish with the celery stalk or pickle spear if using.
56181cf7-1d3c-409d-80eb-80a9c1927c0f Enjoy.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Gather the ingredients. Heat the oven to 350 F. Grease an 8-inch square baking pan and set aside.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 In a large bowl, combine the melted butter, sugar and vanilla extract.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Add the eggs and beat well to combine.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 In another large bowl combine the flour, unsweetened cocoa powder, baking powder, and salt.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Gradually add the flour mixture to the egg mixture, beating until well blended.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Spread the brownie batter evenly into the prepared baking pan.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Sprinkle the chopped fresh strawberries evenly on top of the batter. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Cool completely in the pan on a wire rack.
2ed37d6f-373c-4179-be23-9c8f7be15701 Once cooled, melt the white chocolate and drizzle over the brownies.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Gather the ingredients.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Warm the milk to between 105 F and 115 F. In a small bowl, combine the warm milk, yeast, and 1 teaspoon of the sugar, stirring to dissolve yeast. Let stand 5 minutes to allow it to foam.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 In the bowl of a stand mixer fitted with the dough hook attachment, combine the flour, 1/4 cup of the butter, salt, orange zest, eggs, and the remaining 1/4 cup sugar in bowl of heavy-duty electric stand mixer. Add the milk mixture and beat at low speed 1 to 2 minutes or until blended. Increase speed to medium-low and beat 5 minutes or until the dough is smooth. The dough will be soft and slightly sticky.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Place the dough in a greased bowl, turning over once to grease the top. Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 45 minutes to 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Meanwhile, make the filling. In a small bowl, combine the orange marmalade, 3/4 cup sugar, and 1/3 cup melted butter.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 When the dough is ready, turn out on a lightly floured surface. Roll into a 15 x 12-inch rectangle.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Spread the marmalade mixture over the dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Roll up, jelly-roll style, starting at the long side.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Cut the dough into 12 slices, and place in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. To create a clean cut without compressing the individual rolls, slice each piece using unflavored dental floss rather than a knife. First, score the roll to ensure evenly-sized orange rolls. Slide a long piece of dental floss under the log of dough. When you have the floss where you’d like to make the cut, cross the two ends over the top of the dough and pull them in opposite directions, slicing through the dough.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Cover and let rise 45 minutes or until almost doubled in bulk.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 While the rolls are baking, make the glaze. In a large bowl, combine the cream cheese and butter until light and fluffy.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Frost the rolls and serve.
96d85f74-6147-4813-8407-267f1fef6c15 Enjoy!
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Gather the ingredients.
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Muddle the raspberries, sugar, and lime juice in a cocktail shaker.
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Fill with ice and add cachaca.
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Shake vigorously.
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Strain into a Champagne flute.
2c188732-4585-4e18-999d-8818836bdb79 Top with Champagne.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Gather the ingredients.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Build the liquid ingredients in a highball glass over ice cubes. Start by pouring the vodka, and then add the tomato juice, lemon juice, and the dash of Worcheshire sauce.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Add the celery salt, pepper, and hot sauce to taste. If using, add the horseradish.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Stir well, or try rolling the drink.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Taste and adjust the seasonings to your liking.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Garnish with a lemon wedge and celery stalk or pickle.
a8ede55e-3056-45e8-a7a9-7a56e848d592 Serve and enjoy.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Preheat an oven to 350 F.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Trim the leek: cut off and discard the root end and the dark green stems (reserve the stems to use in broth or stock if that's how you roll). Cut the remaining leek in half lengthwise, then thinly slice crosswise. Put the sliced leek in a bowl and cover with cool water. Swish around to loosen any dirt or grit. Let sit while you attend to the asparagus.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Trim off and discard the tough ends of the asparagus spears. Slice the spears into 1/2-inch pieces.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f In a large frying pan over medium-high heat, melt the butter. Lift the sliced leeks out of the water and put in the pan (don't drain the leeks into a colander—you'll dump all the dirt back on them!). Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of the salt and cook, stirring frequently, until tender, about 3 minutes.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Add the asparagus. Cook, stirring frequently, until just tender, 2 to 3 minutes. Set aside.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f In a medium bowl, whisk the eggs and egg yolks together.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Brush some of the egg onto the pie crust just to coat it. Bake for 5 minutes. Let cool to room temperature.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f While the crust bakes, whisk the milk into the eggs. Whisk in the remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Set the pie crust on a baking sheet for easy handling. Spread the leek and asparagus mixture in the pie crust. Sprinkle with black pepper. Layer on the grated cheese. Pour the egg-milk mixture evenly over everything.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Bake until just set (the very middle can be just a tad jiggly), about 35 minutes.
e25a85a4-0556-49f0-aff2-ef8a6144c51f Let the quiche sit at least 10 minutes before slicing. Serve warm, at room temperature, or even chilled the next day.
f33993d2-ef4b-4fe4-a78e-952772f028ce Gather the ingredients.
f33993d2-ef4b-4fe4-a78e-952772f028ce Fill a highball glass with ice and orange juice.
f33993d2-ef4b-4fe4-a78e-952772f028ce Slowly pour grenadine over the juice. It will sink to the bottom and slowly rise to the top as you drink.
f33993d2-ef4b-4fe4-a78e-952772f028ce Garnish with an orange slice.
f33993d2-ef4b-4fe4-a78e-952772f028ce Serve and enjoy!
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 To make shortbread tails you will need a 23cm (9") round tin, a fluted tin gives the shortbread a lovely crimped edge but don't feel you have to use one. Grease with a little of the butter from the recipe.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Heat the oven to 325 F/160 C/Gas Mark 3.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 In a large baking bowl, place the butter, the sugar, salt, and the lavender drops.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Beat thoroughly using an electric whisk until the mixture is soft, light and creamy.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Add the lemon rind and give the mixture and quick mix.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Sieve in the flour, followed by the cornflour (starch), stir through until completely incorporated.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Press the biscuit mixture into the tin making sure it is into the edges and even on the top.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Sprinkle with a little caster sugar and bake for 30 to 35 minutes until the shortbread is light, golden brown.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Remove the cake from the oven and place onto a cooling tray.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Using a sharp knife, mark the shortbread into 12 wedges and leave to cool completely in the tin.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Once completely cold, carefully remove the wedges from the tin and store in an airtight tin.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 The shortbread keeps well for several days.
348346c1-a06a-4390-9199-3df613499d15 Serve alongside fresh summer fruits, and whipped cream, a trifle, or put your feet up and enjoy with a nice cup of tea.
43bd7171-bae7-4ff4-9c17-2e2e2552ca81 Gather the ingredients.
43bd7171-bae7-4ff4-9c17-2e2e2552ca81 In a large pitcher, mix the wine, blueberries, and frozen pink lemonade together.
43bd7171-bae7-4ff4-9c17-2e2e2552ca81 Allow the flavors to marry in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.
43bd7171-bae7-4ff4-9c17-2e2e2552ca81 Pour into Champagne flutes and top each glass with lemon-lime soda.
43bd7171-bae7-4ff4-9c17-2e2e2552ca81 Serve and enjoy!
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 Preheat oven to 450 F
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 Beat the eggs and milk together until smooth.
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 Add the flour, sugar, lemon zest, and vanilla and mix until there aren't any lumps. Mix completely and quickly, trying to form a froth if possible.
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 Place a skillet in the oven with the butter while it heats.
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 When butter is melted, pour the batter into the skillet. Bake for about 15 minutes until fluffy, golden, and not jiggly.
722cdd13-629e-4999-b8cc-869bd8e1c4e5 Whisk together the ingredients for the glaze. Pour the glaze over the hot dutch baby and serve immediately. You can also top with more powdered sugar if you wish!
59354bdf-0181-46f1-ad9a-463e03d97018 Wet the rims of two cocktail glasses using sliced lime.
59354bdf-0181-46f1-ad9a-463e03d97018 Mix together the coarse salt and chili powder in a low plate. Dip the rims of the glasses into the salt/spice mixture, completely coating each rim.
59354bdf-0181-46f1-ad9a-463e03d97018 Fill each glass with ice.
59354bdf-0181-46f1-ad9a-463e03d97018 In another container (preferably a measuring cup or cocktail shaker) mix or shake together the tomato juice, lime juice, tequila, and hot sauce until completely combined. If you are adding celery salt of Worcestershire sauce you can add it at this time as well.
59354bdf-0181-46f1-ad9a-463e03d97018 Divide the tomato mixture between the two glasses. Top off each glass with the Mexican lager. Stir gently. Add the lime wedges as a garnish to the rim of each glass.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Gather the ingredients.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Grease a 2-quart baking dish or spray with nonstick cooking spray.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Whisk together the eggs, milk, and seasoning in a 9- by13-inch baking dish.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Arrange bread pieces in the baking dish; top with the sliced sausage then cheese.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Cover and refrigerate overnight or let stand for 15 minutes and bake. If you refrigerate overnight, give the casserole about 20 to 30 minutes to come to room temperature before baking.
73e1dca1-0b1f-4c06-9500-638265bf8d1f Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, until firm and lightly browned around the edges.
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Preheat the oven to 450 F.
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Beat the eggs and milk together with a whisk until smooth.
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Add the flour, salt sugar, and vanilla into the egg mixture and whisk until there aren't any lumps, but be careful no to over mix.
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Place 2 tablespoons of butter in an 8-inch cast-iron skillet. Place the skillet in the oven to melt the butter.
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 When butter is melted, swirl it in the pan to evenly coat the surface. Make sure to use a pot holder!! Then pour the batter into the skillet. Bake on the middle rack for about 15 minutes until fluffy and not jiggly. Make sure to move the other oven racks out of the way of the pan. This pancake gets very puffy!
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Sprinkle with powdered sugar, cinnamon sugar, maple syrup or fresh fruit!
17e4c9ab-f1b4-4707-94a6-7e4abe346847 Slice it like a pie and serve individual slices!
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Gather the ingredients.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Heat the oven to 350 F.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Line a 7-inch cake tin with parchment or greaseproof paper.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Divide the almond paste into three portions and take one portion and roll it into a round the size of the cake tin.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde In a large, roomy baking bowl, mix the mixed dried fruits and candied peel with the flour, salt, and spices.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde In another large bowl, cream the butter with the sugar, until light and fluffy.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Add the beaten egg to the butter mixture a little bit at a time, beating well after each addition — don't try to rush this process as the batter could curdle. If it does, add a tablespoon of the flour and mix again, this should bring the mixture back together.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Carefully fold in half the flour and half the fruit into the egg and butter mixture, once incorporated repeat with the remaining flour and fruit.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Put half of the cake mixture into the tin, smooth and cover with the round of almond paste.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Put the remaining cake mixture into the tin and smooth the surface carefully.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Bake in the center of the oven for 1 hour.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Lower the heat to 300 F and bake for 1 1/2 hours more or (depending on your oven), until the cake is golden brown. To check if the cake is cooked, insert a skewer into the cake, it should come out clean and dry. If it is, remove from the oven and leave to cool in the tin. If not, cook it a little longer.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Roll another third of almond paste, again to the size of the tin. Make the remaining almond paste equally into 11 tiny balls.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Once the cake is completely cold, remove from the tin and brush the top of the cake with apricot jam and cover with the disc of almond paste.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Place the 11 tiny balls evenly around the edge. Brush them all over with a little apricot jam.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Place under a hot grill until lightly browned.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Decorate the cake as you wish with tiny Easter eggs or any other Easter theme.
143158a2-f123-49be-97ab-847b3afe1bde Serve and enjoy!
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Gather the ingredients.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Heat the oven to 425 F/220 C/Gas 7. When the oven is nearly preheated, put the butter in a 2-quart baking dish and put it in the oven to melt. Watch carefully to make sure the butter doesn't become too brown. It should be hot and begin foamy, but not browned.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b In a small bowl, combine the flour, sugar, and salt. Mix well to blend ingredients.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b In a medium mixing bowl, whisk the milk and eggs together until well blended.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Whisk the flour mixture into the milk and egg mixture. Beat with the whisk until the batter is smooth.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Remove the baking dish with the hot butter from the oven and place it on a rack. Pour the batter into the pan.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Sprinkle blueberries over the batter.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Bake for 14 to 17 minutes, until the pancake, is puffed and golden brown.
e752f751-38e6-4c91-880d-acd0786a928b Sift powdered sugar over the pancake and serve with more butter and maple syrup or fruit syrup.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Gather the ingredients.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Tear the bread into bite-size pieces to equal 6 cups, firmly packed.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Combine the eggs, whipping cream, half-and-half, onion, Mexican cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, chilies, and pimiento in a large bowl.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Gently stir in the bread pieces.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Pour the bread mixture into lightly greased 9-inch-deep pie plates.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Bake at 425 F for 20 to 22 minutes or until browned and set.
c503171e-280e-4a87-ba52-d3e3728a5d78 Serve immediately.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Preheat the oven to 350 F.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 In a large mixing bowl, mix the eggs, cheese, parsley, salt, and pepper. Set aside.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Heat the olive oil in a large, heavy-bottomed pot or Dutch oven over medium heat. Add the lamb and onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until meat is browned and about half cooked about 5 minutes.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Stir in the tomatoes and vegetable and continue to cook for another minute.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Transfer the lamb and vegetable mixture to a baking pan (you can also use a large cast-iron skillet) large enough to hold it (and the eggs), and pour the egg mixture evenly over the top.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Shake the pan a bit to distribute the eggs evenly through all the nooks and crannies, then bake just until set, about 10 minutes.
d71851d8-0c60-4984-814e-6c6ce8388310 Serve hot or at room temperature.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Gather the ingredients.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Make the chimichurri sauce first. Whisk together the fresh parsley, cilantro, olive oil, lime juice, garlic, a teaspoon of the salt, and the crushed red pepper flakes in a small bowl. You can also process this sauce in the food processor for a finer minced sauce. You can do this step up to a day ahead of time. The longer it sits, the more flavorful it will get.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Generously salt and pepper both sides of the steak.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Heat a cast iron skillet or another heavy-bottomed pan on high heat. Once hot, add a tablespoon of butter to the pan and add the steak. Sear on high heat for 3 minutes. Do not move until the three minutes are up. This will guarantee good color and an even sear.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Flip the steak and add the other tablespoon of butter to the pan and crack the two eggs onto the other side of the pan. Generously season the eggs with salt and pepper too. You can fry them in a different pan if you wish.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Cook the steak and the eggs another 3 minutes for medium rare. You’ll know the eggs are done when the whites are set and the yolks are still jiggly. Heat for longer if you want a more well done steak. You can also flip the eggs if you like them over easy.
fddc4105-2832-47f2-8f22-fcc8d30b7dd5 Top the steak with the chimichurri sauce and serve with a little hot sauce if you like. Wait a few minutes to allow the steak to rest before slicing. Enjoy!
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Gather the ingredients.
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Roughly chop the tomatoes, shallot, and chile (if using).
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 In a blender or food processor, whirl them until smooth, at least 1 minute to get everything puréed. Do this in batches if necessary.
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Run the pureed mixture through a sieve or food mill for a smoother texture.
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Add the lemon juice. Stir to combine, and add salt, pepper, hot sauce or horseradish, and more lemon juice (or anything else!) to taste. Tasting is key to end up with a cocktail that meets your ideal version of a Bloody Mary.
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Cover and chill the spiced-up tomato juice mixture until cold, at least an hour and up to two days.
dfc8253d-c4a9-48bc-8608-fc202c8a6908 Pour the juice into 2 to 4 glasses, add 2 tablespoons (or more, no judgment here!) vodka or gin into each glass, if you like, and stir to combine. Garnish with celery stalk and/or pickled green beans.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Gather your ingredients. Preheat the oven to 375 F.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca If using fresh chorizo, brown it in a medium sized skillet on high heat for about 5 minutes or until the sausage is cooked through and browned. Stir as you are cooking.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Spread out the tortilla chips onto a parchment paper lined-baking sheet.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Cover the chips with the shredded cheese and the cooked chorizo.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Make 6 little wells in the chips and crack an egg into each one. Sprinkle salt and pepper over the top.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Place the baking sheet into the oven on the lowest rack. Cook until the egg whites are cooked through and the yolks are to your desired doneness, about 15 minutes.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Add more cheese to the top if you wish.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Drizzle the taco sauce over the top of the nachos and top with the sliced avocado and cherry tomatoes.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Top with the sour cream, sliced jalapenos, and any of the garnishes that you want. The scallions, cilantro, and lime all add great flavor and color.
ad1f205d-de1d-4a4d-b643-f6a8093a7dca Serve immediately with more sour cream and taco sauce!
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Gather the ingredients.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da You will notice a thin, silvery membrane on the underside of the ribs. If it isn't removed, it will stay tough and chewy and might prevent some of your dry rub spices from penetrating the meat. To remove the membrane, slide a butter knife under it on one end until you can grasp it. With a paper towel in hand (to keep it from slipping), slowly pull on the membrane to remove it in one piece.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da In a small bowl, combine the smoked paprika, chili powder, onion powder, dry mustard, garlic powder, salt, black pepper, and cayenne. Blend the spices thoroughly and then rub the mixture all over the ribs.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Place a trivet in the Instant Pot and add the 1 cup of stock or water and the apple cider vinegar. Stand the ribs on end in the pot, coiling them to fit. Lock the lid in place and make sure the steam release valve is in the sealing position. Choose the pressure cook or manual function (high pressure) and set the time for 25 minutes.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da When the ribs are done, carefully turn the steam release valve to the venting position for a quick release. If your pressure cooker is not an Instant Pot, follow the manufacturer's directions for a quick release.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Line a large baking sheet with foil and preheat the broiler (or grill).
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Remove the ribs to the prepared baking sheet and brush generously with barbecue sauce. Broil or grill the ribs until they are lightly charred.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Slice the ribs into individual ribs or serving-size portions.
b0198f54-e09e-4a8b-b02f-4929cfa0d7da Enjoy!
31673b15-9eb8-4f8d-b615-0b8a9810bb85 Gather the ingredients.
31673b15-9eb8-4f8d-b615-0b8a9810bb85 In a pint glass, combine the jalapeño syrup, tequila, and fruit juices. Stir well.
31673b15-9eb8-4f8d-b615-0b8a9810bb85 Fill the glass with ice (if desired) and top with beer.
31673b15-9eb8-4f8d-b615-0b8a9810bb85 Serve and enjoy!
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Gather your ingredients.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Trim off the excess fat from the edge of the pork chop. Pound each pork chop between two sheets of parchment paper to ¼ inch thickness. Salt and pepper both sides of the pork chops. Set aside.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Whisk together the flour, half of the parmesan cheese, and a pinch of the salt and pepper into a shallow bowl.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Whisk together the egg, a pinch of the salt and pepper and 2 tablespoons of water into another shallow bowl.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Whisk together the remaining parmesan cheese, panko bread crumbs, dried basil, dried oregano and another pinch of salt and pepper in a third shallow bowl.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Dip the pork chops into the flour/cheese mixture. Coat both sides and then shake off the excess flour.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Then dip the pork into the egg mixture and flip to coat both sides.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Transfer the pork chop to the breadcrumb mixture and coat both sides.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Heat the olive oil and butter in a large skillet on medium heat until the butter has melted. Add the pork chops and cook on medium heat for about 3 minutes or until golden brown. Flip and cook for another 3-4 minutes or until the internal temperature reaches 165F.
b64ca440-93df-4d74-9051-089a7e18538d Remove from the heat and serve with arugula, more parmesan, chopped parsley and lemon wedges.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 Gather the ingredients.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 Cut the pork shoulder (aka pork butt or Boston butt) into several large chunks and add it to the slow cooker along with the sliced onion, salt, pepper, and root beer. Place the cover on the slow cooker and cook on the low setting for 8 to 10 hours, or until the pork is very tender. Alternatively, choose the high setting and cook the pork for about 4 to 5 hours.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 When the pork is ready, drain and discard the liquids. Use two forks or a potato masher to shred the pork. Add the barbecue sauce and stir to blend.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 For a classic pulled pork sandwich, pile the shredded pork on a bun or hoagie roll and top with sliced dill or sour pickles and coleslaw.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 Serve pulled pork sandwiches with extra barbecue sauce and coleslaw on the side.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 Alternatively, use the shredded pulled pork to make tacos, or serve it as an entree along with mac and cheese, slaw, and biscuits.
59af19fa-9fc9-46ca-a82e-bbcefbc33b78 Enjoy!
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Gather the ingredients.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Preheat the oven to 400 F or the grill to medium-high (about 400 F). If using frozen shrimp place the package under cold water for 10 minutes to thaw.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Bring 2 quarts of water to a roaring boil and add the potatoes and the corn. Reduce the heat and bring to simmer. Cook for 10 minutes on simmer and drain into a colander. Set aside.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 While the potatoes and corn are simmering prepare 4 sets of 12 x 24 inch long aluminum foil sheets. Fold each in half, forming a square. If using industrial aluminum foil simply prepare sheets measuring 12 x 12 inches. Slightly fold up the edges of the sheets.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 In a large bowl combine the drained potatoes and corn, the sausage, the thawed shrimp, the onion, and the garlic. Drizzle with the 4 tablespoons of melted butter, season with salt, pepper, and Old Bay seasoning. Mix very well to coat all ingredients.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Divide the shrimp boil ingredients between the four aluminum foil sheets.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Neatly fold into packets.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Place them onto a baking sheet and bake for 15 minutes. If grilling, place the packets directly onto the grill surface and cook for 15 minutes, flipping once after about 8 minutes.
7eaf5d09-59fe-42fe-a3b6-b9683177d562 Serve the packets slightly opened up, garnished with chopped parsley, a pinch of Old Bay seasoning and a few lemon wedges. Serve the 1 stick melted butter as a side for optional drizzling over the shrimp boil or dipping.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Gather the ingredients.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Cook the linguine pasta according to the package instructions. Drain, but keep back 2 tablespoons of the cooking water. Toss the pasta in the pan you cooked it in with the reserved cooking water and 1 tablespoon of the olive oil. Keep warm.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Make the sauce while the pasta is cooking. Heat the remaining olive oil in a large heavy-bottomed frying pan to hot, but not smoking.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Add the minced shallot and cook for 1 minute. Add the chili flakes and stir. Lower the heat slightly and add the garlic. Stir well and cook for one minute. Take great care to not burn the garlic or the the dish will taste bitter.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Heat a serving bowl - this will ultimately ensure that the dish keeps warm while you enjoy it.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Add the drained sardines to the frying pan and stir very carefully taking care not to break the sardines up too much. Finally, add the lemon zest and stir again.
f553f238-37d4-4f12-9a9b-b07582971655 Tip the cooked linguine into the warmed serving bowl, stir the sardine sauce, parsley, and baby kale (the heat of the pasta and the sauce will be enough to cook the tiny leaves) into the linguine. Add salt and pepper to taste. Finish with a drizzle of lemon juice and serve immediately.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Gather the ingredients.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Remove the roast from the roasting pan and let it rest, covered with foil, on a cutting board in an area that's warm. If there is a lot of fat left in the pan, pour most of it off—you can refrigerate it in a Mason jar to add concentrated flavor and richness to soups, stocks, chilis, and even pasta. When pouring out the fat, take care not to lose any of the meat juices.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Place the roasting pan on the stovetop, across two burners, and add the chopped carrots, onion, and celery.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Cook on high for a minute, stirring everything around with a wooden spoon until the veggies are a bit browned and most of the liquid has cooked off—but don't let anything burn.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Pour in about half of the stock and cook for another minute over high heat while scraping all those toasty bits (called fond) away from the bottom of the pan with your wooden spoon.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Pour the contents of the roasting pan into a large saucepan along with the remaining stock. Simmer for about 20 minutes or until the liquid has reduced by about a third.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Pour the liquid through a mesh strainer. For a finer strain, you can line the strainer with cheesecloth. Let it sit for a couple of minutes so that you can skim off any fat that rises to the top.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 By now, your roast will have finished resting and will be ready to carve. If the roast has thrown off any additional juices while it rested, stir these into the sauce.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Add salt and pepper to taste.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Each portion of meat should get 1 1/2 to 2 ounces of au jus sauce.
5cadfb1a-72e9-4b92-8ee5-664aa4ee9b47 Serve warm and enjoy.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Gather the ingredients.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Make sure your grill is clean. Rub the cooking grate with a thin layer of oil—1 or 2 teaspoons should be enough. Heat the grill (whether charcoal, gas, or electric) to medium-high. You should be able to hold your hand about 1 inch above the cooking grate for 3 to 4 seconds before pulling it away from the heat. A properly heated grill will help keep the fish from sticking excessively while also cooking it gently and thoroughly without setting it aflame.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 While the grill heats, prepare the salmon fillets. Rinse them and pat them dry.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Use tweezers to pull out any pin bones. Pull them out in the direction at which they're coming out for the smoothest results. Don't see any pin bones? Run your finger down the "seam" of the fillet—you'll feel them.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Brush the cooking grate with another 1 to 2 teaspoons of oil. Brush the 4 fillets with the remaining oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Place the salmon, skin-side-down, on the hot grill and cover. Cook, undisturbed, until the salmon just starts to release its fat (opaque mayonnaise-like stuff), or until it reaches 145 F, which takes about 15 to 20 minutes for most 1-inch thick fillets. Allow another 5 to 10 minutes for each extra inch of thickness. Use a spatula to remove the fish from the grill.
f051d0fb-cc91-4140-8fe6-82cdd3df7c46 Serve grilled salmon immediately. Offer lemon wedges so people can spritz their salmon with fresh lemon juice, or serve with the garnish of your choice.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 Gather the ingredients.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 In a large resealable food storage bag (plastic), combine the oil, vinegar, sugar, ketchup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic, and Tabasco. Add the chicken and turn to coat thoroughly. Seal the bag and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 Pour marinade into a saucepan and bring to a full rolling boil over high heat. Remove from the heat and set aside.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 Heat the grill to moderate or medium-high heat, about 350 F to 375 F.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 First, sear the chicken over direct heat for about 2 to 3 minutes per side.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 Continue grilling the chicken leg quarters over indirect heat -- not directly over coals or gas burners -- turning frequently and basting with the reserved boiled marinade, for about 35 to 55 minutes, depending on size.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 The chicken should be fork tender and juices will run clear. The temperature should register at least 165 F on an instant-read thermometer inserted into the thickest part of the meat but not touching bone.
72572afd-acec-46c8-8b70-ffcb5c25e0b8 Serve and enjoy!
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Gather the ingredients.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Build the liquid ingredients in a highball glass over ice cubes. Start by pouring the vodka, and then add the tomato juice, lemon juice, and the dash of Worcheshire sauce.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Add the celery salt, pepper, and hot sauce to taste. If using, add the horseradish.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Stir well, or try rolling the drink.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Taste and adjust the seasonings to your liking.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Garnish with a lemon wedge and celery stalk or pickle.
b64517c0-9d5f-4354-9d45-36d813afd6be Serve and enjoy.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Gather the ingredients.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Cook the ziti in boiling salted water following the package directions. Drain well and set aside.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Heat the oven to 350 F (180 C/Gas 4). Lightly butter a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b While the ziti is cooking, drizzle the olive oil in a large skillet or sauté pan and place it over medium heat. When the oil is hot, add the ground beef, onion, and green bell pepper. Cook, stirring until the onion is tender and the beef is no longer pink.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Drain off the excess fat and then add the tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, oregano, garlic powder, salt, and pepper. Bring to a simmer.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Add the cooked pasta and half of the mozzarella cheese.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Transfer the mixture to the prepared baking dish.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Top the casserole with the remaining mozzarella cheese.
6cc04b83-fd76-477f-97d2-428cdca43e1b Bake the ziti casserole for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Gather the ingredients.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 To make the brine, combine salt, white sugar, and hot water in a large plastic or glass container that you can cover. Stir to mix. Add cold water and cayenne, if using. Continue stirring to dissolve.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Add chicken drumsticks, cover, and refrigerate for 4 hours.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Meanwhile, gather the ingredients for the sauce.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Make barbecue sauce by combining ingredients in a medium saucepan.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Remove from heat and allow to cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Preheat grill to a medium-low heat (around 275 F/135 C).
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Remove the chicken legs from the brine and discard brine. Rinse chicken thoroughly to remove all traces of the brine from the surface. Pat dry with paper towels.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Grill chicken legs for about 30 to 35 minutes, turning often (about every 5 minutes) to make sure all sides are cooked evenly.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 During the last 15 to 20 minutes, start brushing sauce over the surface every 5 minutes, rotating the chicken to coat evenly, until the chicken is done (an internal temperature of should be at least 165 F/75 C, but you may want to get closer to 180 F/82 C), and the sauce has cooked down to a sticky consistency.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Remove chicken from heat, place on a large serving platter, and tent loosely with aluminum foil. Let drumsticks rest for 5 to 7 minutes.
646079a5-84c2-4dde-b4e6-510f0ee5f020 Serve and enjoy!
b5fc721f-cd86-4aed-9c82-5f70dbd3c7c3 In a large bowl, add the ground lamb, diced onion, minced garlic, chopped parsley, ground cumin, ground coriander, ground cinnamon, salt, and pepper. Mix together until thoroughly combined and form four individual patties.
b5fc721f-cd86-4aed-9c82-5f70dbd3c7c3 Heat up your grill or a grill pan if cooking indoors. Place the burgers on the grill and cook for 4 minutes, flip and cook for an additional 4 minutes. That will give you a medium-rare burger and an internal temperature of about 160 degrees Fahrenheit. Cook for an additional minute or two if you'd like your burgers more well done.
b5fc721f-cd86-4aed-9c82-5f70dbd3c7c3 Toast or grill the buns until lightly golden brown (optional) and spread about a tablespoon of labneh on the bottom half of each bun. Place a cooked burger over the labneh, top with the lettuce or green of your choice and sprinkle the crumbled feta cheese over it. top with the remaining half of the bun and serve hot.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d In a medium bowl, combine the breadcrumbs, milk, salt, pepper, marjoram, and ketchup; mix well with a spoon and let this mixture stand for 5 minutes.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d Add the ground beef, crumbling it with your fingers as you add it; mix gently but thoroughly with your hands until combined.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d Form the meat mixture into about 10 to 12 mini burgers. At this point, you can cover the burgers and chill them for up to 24 hours.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d When you are ready to eat, prepare and preheat a gas or charcoal grill. Grill the burgers on a small rack placed over the regular grill rack, over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes per side, turning once, until the burgers are 160 F.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d Top each mini burger with the American cheese slices and cover the grill for 30 to 40 seconds to let the cheese melt. You can also fry these burgers in a hot pan over medium-high heat, turning once, until done to 160 F.
2e323db3-4cbb-418f-b51f-f8a141ea502d Assemble the burgers with the buns, tomatoes, lettuce leaves, ketchup, mustard, and pickles.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Gather the ingredients.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Begin by forming your lamb patties.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 You can either cook it on a cast-iron skillet or you can cook it on the grill. Either way, get the heat source blazing hot.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Add your burger sphere, let it cook for a few minutes until the bottom becomes crispy and cooked about halfway up the meat.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 At this point, flip the burger gently, and then brown the other side for a minute or two.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Next, you'll want to take a spatula and smush the burger. The grilled bits will help the burger stay together and will taste amazing. Continue cooking until the meat is cooked through and set aside to let it rest.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Then, toast your bun. Do this either directly on the grill, in a toaster, or using a broiler.
6fedc11e-9613-4235-8f47-63b6721601c1 Once the bun is crispy and warm, smear half the tzatziki onto both halves. On the bottom half, add the lamb burger, then the roasted tomatoes, then the red onion, and the mint. Serve immediately.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Gather the ingredients.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff The night before you plan to serve your prime rib, mix salt, pepper, and rosemary and rub the meat with it liberally.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Cover the meat and place it in the refrigerator overnight.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff The roast needs to come to room temperature before frying, so remember to remove it from the refrigerator around an hour to an hour and a half before frying.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Heat 3 gallons of peanut oil to 360 F.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Slowly lower the prime rib into 350 F oil. You can expect the oil to drop in temperature quickly, probably down to approximately 325 F. Turn the heat up on the burner to bring back up to 350 F and then level off temperature.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Cook the prime rib for 3 minutes per pound of weight for medium-rare steaks or 4 minutes per pound for medium.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Carefully remove from hot oil and let rest for 10 minutes.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Try using sliced bread to drain on versus paper towels.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Let rest for a few minutes and then slice.
1f20b913-d645-40e9-8b71-7abe5c1fbaff Serve and enjoy!
7b2eaf85-4caa-4493-81a9-5d21772d8b6e Preheat oven to 400 degrees F. Spray a 2- or 3-quart baking dish with cooking spray.
7b2eaf85-4caa-4493-81a9-5d21772d8b6e Whisk together the mayonnaise and mustard. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
7b2eaf85-4caa-4493-81a9-5d21772d8b6e Brush the mayonnaise-mustard mixture over both sides of the halibut.
7b2eaf85-4caa-4493-81a9-5d21772d8b6e Spread the potato chip crumbs out in a shallow dish or on a plate. Dip both sides of the halibut in the potato chip crumbs.
7b2eaf85-4caa-4493-81a9-5d21772d8b6e Place in the prepared baking dish. Bake 18-22 minutes, until fish flakes easily with a fork.
4e9eb118-7678-46ac-b755-4f0ad720ca9b Sauté the onion slices in butter until tender; set aside.
4e9eb118-7678-46ac-b755-4f0ad720ca9b Shape the ground beef into four patties; fry in ​a skillet or broil to desired doneness, turning to evenly brown.
4e9eb118-7678-46ac-b755-4f0ad720ca9b Place hamburger patties on the rye bread slices on a broiler rack. Top the burgers with sauerkraut, onion, and cheese. Broil until cheese is melted.
4e9eb118-7678-46ac-b755-4f0ad720ca9b Serve with Thousand Island dressing or pickle slices if desired.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Gather the ingredients.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Combine ground pork, ground veal, pork fat, and bread.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Whisk together salt, pepper, cayenne pepper, nutmeg, mace, thyme, marjoram, sage, lemon zest, and egg.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Knead into pork and veal mixture.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Stuff sausage mixture into prepared casings, compacting firmly.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Prick any air pockets with a pin. (Store raw sausages in the refrigerator up to 3 days. Freeze up to 3 months.*)
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e To serve, poach, braise, or fry the bangers.
be5ef65f-39ed-4961-a2d7-a35d5baf576e Pair with mashed potatoes and enjoy!
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Gather the ingredients.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Heat the oven to 400 F (200 C/Gas 6). Rinse the flounder with cold water and pat dry with paper towels.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 In a medium bowl, combine the crab meat with the chopped green bell pepper, pimiento, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, Old Bay, cayenne pepper (if using), and crushed crackers.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 In a small bowl or cup, combine the egg white, 1 tablespoon of the mayonnaise, and the parsley.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Add to the crab mixture and toss until thoroughly blended.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Brush the flounder fillets on the flat, cut side with some of the melted butter.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Place the flounder in a greased shallow baking dish and top each fillet with even amounts of the crab mixture.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Drizzle the remaining butter over the top of the stuffed fillets.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Bake the crab-topped flounder in the preheated oven for 15 minutes.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Combine the egg yolk and the remaining mayonnaise in a small bowl.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Gently spread the egg mixture on top of each fish portion and sprinkle with paprika.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Increase the oven temperature to 450 F (230 C/Gas 8) and bake 6 minutes longer, or until golden and bubbly.
8e003236-907c-4ff9-81b3-95b30d69d441 Serve and enjoy!
cb63a473-8ca8-4f7b-81ab-fbbc1e2a1bac Place beans in food processor and process them until they are fairly smooth. Add flour, cornmeal, salsa, cumin and garlic salt. Process until well combined.
cb63a473-8ca8-4f7b-81ab-fbbc1e2a1bac Spoon the mixture into six balls on a large plate and refrigerate at least 1 hour or up to 4 hours before cooking.
cb63a473-8ca8-4f7b-81ab-fbbc1e2a1bac Heat barbecue grill or ridged grill pan over medium heat. Coat grill or pan lightly with oil. Form each ball into a 4-inch-wide patty about 1/2-inch thick. Place the patties on the grill or in a pan and then cook until browned and heated through. This should take about 4 to 5 minutes per side.
cb63a473-8ca8-4f7b-81ab-fbbc1e2a1bac Serve your black bean cornmeal patties on hamburger buns with your favorite toppings.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Split your bagel down the middle and toast until crispy.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Meanwhile, crack your eggs into a small bowl, add salt and pepper and whisk vigorously.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Heat a small nonstick frying pan over medium heat, add your butter and allow it to melt.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Pour your whisked eggs into the buttered frypan and stir continuously until the eggs have cooked through but are still soft. Add in the dill and set aside.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Once the bagel is toasted, gently place the soft scrambled eggs on top of the bottom half of the bagel, then add the smoked salmon pieces, the cooked asparagus, and the pickled red onions.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Next, take the remaining top half of the bagel and smear it with cream cheese. Place the creamed cheese bagel half on top of the rest of the sandwich and serve.
869dd47d-3349-4877-96d3-94a0ee6f67c3 Enjoy!
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc Gather the ingredients.
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc Preheat an oven to 400 F. If you haven't had the clams shucked, shuck them yourself: insert a blunt knife or screwdriver into the hinge or otherwise between the shells, twist it to break open the shells, remove the top shell, and repeat with remaining clams.
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc Set the shucked clams on the half-shell (be sure to scrape off any clam meat that clings to the other side of the shell into the side you're cooking—you want all that meat!) on a baking sheet or in a baking dish.
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc Peel the garlic and mince it until it forms almost a paste. Mince the parsley leaves as well.
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc In a small bowl, combine the bread crumbs, garlic, and chile flakes. Mix to combine thoroughly. Drizzle the mixture with the olive oil and combine again. Distribute the stuffing evenly on the clams.
b79ab93e-e9de-4311-a792-a480ecd81ebc Bake until the clams are heated through and the breadcrumb topping is browned, 10 to 12 minutes—10 for slightly softer clams, 12 for those who like their cooked seafood really cooked. Serve the clams right away.
c22a7579-8069-46b4-845f-3e9ffc3a645f Fry 4 slices chopped bacon in a medium pot until soft and golden, about 4 minutes. Add 1 small chopped onion and 2 cloves chopped garlic and continue cooking until the bacon is nicely browned and the onion is tender, about 4 minutes longer.
c22a7579-8069-46b4-845f-3e9ffc3a645f Stir in 3 pounds well-scrubbed Manila clams and add 1 cup beer or water or chicken stock. Cover the pot and steam the clams for 3 to 5 minutes, until they open. Discard any clams that do not open.
c22a7579-8069-46b4-845f-3e9ffc3a645f Stir gently to mix with the bacon, garlic, and onion, and serve immediately.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Gather the ingredients.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f First, preheat oven to 400 F. Pierce the sweet potatoes and microwave them together until they are soft, about 4 to 6 minutes. Mash them firmly into measuring cups to make 2 cups of mashed sweet potatoes, and then transfer them to a medium-sized mixing bowl.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Meanwhile, in a small saucepan, bring 3/4 cup water and the quinoa to a boil. Reduce to a low simmer and cover, until the water is nearly absorbed and the quinoa appears transparent and is fully cooked​ about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove the quinoa from the stove and allow it to sit covered, for about 5 minutes.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f In a separate saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of the vegan butter substitute or butter. Stir in 1 tablespoon of maple syrup and the cayenne pepper. Add mixture to the mashed sweet potatoes along with the kale, the cooked quinoa, pecans and 1/2 teaspoon of salt and then mix it all together well.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Form the mixture into four patties; place on a well-oiled baking sheet. Bake for 35 minutes, turning once at the halfway point.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f When the burgers have around 15 minutes left to bake, make the onion topping. In a small skillet over medium heat, melt the remaining 1 tablespoon vegan butter substitute. Add the onion; sprinkle with salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste. Cook and stir for 12 minutes. Reduce heat to low; add remaining 1 tablespoon of maple syrup. Cook and stir until onions are slightly brown, about 3 more minutes; remove from heat.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Transfer burgers to buns and top each with onion mixture.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Makes four sweet potato veggie burger patties.
836add16-cbdd-4630-82f4-cd09aea4d71f Serve and enjoy!
